description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Neurophysiotherapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 22.5 hrs per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge? We have the exciting opportunity to join the Solihull neuro team, which comprises of Stroke ESD service and neuro out patients. We have created a new static band 6 position to support the changing needs of the service post pandemic. If you are a physiotherapist looking to develop your neurophysiotherapy skills and develop your clinical experience, specialism and leadership skills this could be the post for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Training &amp; Support will be provided by experienced therapists already working within the team, with the focus on developing the skills of the successful candidate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, self-motivated, innovative physiotherapist who is interested in expanding their knowledge and skills &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need good clinical skills, a flexible approach; including excellent team working, organisational and time management skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will join our dynamic team of therapists who strive towards holistic recovery and regaining independence following admission within this teaching Trust. We are committed to continued professional and career development of all staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must beprepared to participate in the departmental 7 day working rota within the teams. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We encourage informal conversation so please feel free to contact: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Linzie Bassett, Clinical team Lead for Stroke and Neuro Therapies Heartlands and Solihull Hospitals. Tel: 0121 424 3771 or on email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Linzie.bassett@heartofengland.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Joanna.kitchen@heartofengland.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; tel 0121 424 4660&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospitals Birmingham NHS Foundation Trust is an equal opportunities employer and enforces a no smoking policy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
